<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3824] Spark SQL should cache in MEMORY_AND_DISK by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3824</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spark SQL currently uses MEMORY_ONLY as the default format. Due to the use of column buffers however, there is a huge cost to having to recompute blocks, much more so than Spark core. Especially since now we are more conservative about caching blocks and sometimes won&apos;t cache blocks we think might exceed memory, it seems good to keep persisted blocks on disk by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
